{"id":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","direction":"ltr","updated":1715644936151,"alternate":[{"type":"text/html","href":"https://www.theverge.com/"}],"items":[{"language":"en","fingerprint":"9a4fef06","id":"jF8788AjyYTDSGnr0rgzJ1ivOGtuQxU9kz47w6Gbeng=_18f74682fd7:1073876:408b12aa","originId":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155982/sony-playstation-co-ceo-hermen-hulst-hideaki-nishino","origin":{"streamId":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","htmlUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/"},"content":{"content":"<figure>\n<img alt=\"An illustration of the PlaySation “PS” logo overlayed on swooping blue and teal colors\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O7ij1ndPaNzW4yRyXUMMqPundAk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345336/acastro_STK097_01.0.jpg\">\n<figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Sony is appointing co-CEOs Hermen Hulst and Hideaki Nishino to lead its PlayStation business <a href=\"https://sonyinteractive.com/en/press-releases/2024/new-leadership-structure-formed-at-sony-interactive-entertainment/\">from June 1st</a>. Hermen Hulst, who currently serves as PlayStation studios chief, will be appointed as CEO of Sony Interactive Entertainment’s (SIE) studio business group. Hideaki Nishino will be appointed CEO of SIE’s platform business group, and both will report up to Sony CFO and SIE chairman Hiroki Totoki.</p>\n<p>The unusual appointment of co-CEOs comes just months after former PlayStation boss <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/27/23893389/sony-playstation-jim-ryan-ceo-steps-down\">Jim Ryan retired</a>. Totoki had been serving as interim CEO of SIE and was working to find the successor for the SIE CEO role, but Sony has now decided it wants to split up responsibilities for leading its PlayStation business across platform and games. Both...</p>\n<p>\n<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155982/sony-playstation-co-ceo-hermen-hulst-hideaki-nishino\">Continue reading…</a>\n</p>","direction":"ltr"},"title":"Sony names new&nbsp;PlayStation&nbsp;leaders following Jim Ryan’s retirement","updated":1715644398000,"crawled":1715644936151,"published":1715644398000,"author":"Tom Warren","alternate":[{"type":"text/html","href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155982/sony-playstation-co-ceo-hermen-hulst-hideaki-nishino"}],"visual":{"processor":"feedly-nikon-v3.1","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O7ij1ndPaNzW4yRyXUMMqPundAk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345336/acastro_STK097_01.0.jpg","width":1310,"height":873},"canonicalUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155982/sony-playstation-co-ceo-hermen-hulst-hideaki-nishino","unread":true,"engagement":36,"engagementRate":1.03,"webfeeds":{"wordmark":"http://storage.googleapis.com/test-site-assets/PSNTZO8gXFUe-cpCZyApw0vEKWPT4b14D6teBEocIAE_owordmark-1503a52ff7f"}},{"language":"en","fingerprint":"d6430bd1","id":"jF8788AjyYTDSGnr0rgzJ1ivOGtuQxU9kz47w6Gbeng=_18f7432e3b9:103e798:408b12aa","originId":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155775/dyson-washg1-mop-price-specs-release-date","origin":{"streamId":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","htmlUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/"},"content":{"content":"<figure>\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5FCT38SDOmZyyGUOwsMeYcMkbhU=/0x20:480x340/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345261/WR01_IRSBLBLKBLK_033_RGB_InUse_TableChairs_DownLow_Debris_WoodFloor_1Drop_Hand_A4_MIX.0.png\">\n<figcaption><em>The Dyson WashG1 can wipe up wet messes.</em> | Image: Dyson</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Dyson’s newest device for dealing with dirt in your home is a mechanical mop. Unlike the British engineering company’s flagship fans, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24063308/dyson-supersonic-r-hairdryer-beauty-tech\">hair dryers</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24098771/dyson-vis-nav-robot-vacuum-hands-on\">vacuums</a>, the new Dyson WashG1 floor washing machine doesn’t use precision-engineered fans or a fine-tuned <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2021/10/4/22708470/dyson-robot-vacuum-cleaner-us-fcc-filing\">Hyperdymium motor</a>. Instead, the mop relies on mechanical agitation to clean up wet spills, picks up dirt and debris, and gives your hard floors a really good wash. </p>\n<p>The WashG1 wet floor cleaner — aka mop — costs $699.99 and is the company’s first dedicated mopping device. The cordless, battery-powered mop is slated for release this fall, and you can sign up to be notified when the world’s fanciest mop arrives <a rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&xs=1&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dyson.com%2Fwet-cleaning%2Fwashg1&referrer=theverge.com&sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F5%2F13%2F24155775%2Fdyson-washg1-mop-price-specs-release-date\" target=\"_blank\">on Dyson’s site</a>. </p>\n<div><aside><div data-anthem-component=\"readmore\" data-anthem-component-data=\"{&quot;stories&quot;:[{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Dyson’s 360 Vis Nav is a powerful robovac&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/24098771/dyson-vis-nav-robot-vacuum-hands-on&quot;},{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A trip to Dyson’s dirt-filled, germ-obsessed world &quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/22/23732748/dyson-hq-factory-singapore-tour-new-vacuums-purifier-robovac&quot;}]}\"></div></aside></div>\n<p>While it’s definitely fancy, this isn’t a smart mop —...</p>\n<p>\n<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155775/dyson-washg1-mop-price-specs-release-date\">Continue reading…</a>\n</p>","direction":"ltr"},"title":"The WashG1 is Dyson’s first mop","updated":1715641260000,"crawled":1715641443257,"published":1715641260000,"author":"Jennifer Pattison Tuohy","alternate":[{"type":"text/html","href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155775/dyson-washg1-mop-price-specs-release-date"}],"visual":{"processor":"feedly-nikon-v3.1","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5FCT38SDOmZyyGUOwsMeYcMkbhU=/0x20:480x340/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345261/WR01_IRSBLBLKBLK_033_RGB_InUse_TableChairs_DownLow_Debris_WoodFloor_1Drop_Hand_A4_MIX.0.png","width":1310,"height":873},"canonicalUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155775/dyson-washg1-mop-price-specs-release-date","unread":true,"engagement":17,"engagementRate":0.47,"webfeeds":{"wordmark":"http://storage.googleapis.com/test-site-assets/PSNTZO8gXFUe-cpCZyApw0vEKWPT4b14D6teBEocIAE_owordmark-1503a52ff7f"}},{"language":"en","fingerprint":"1b332fd7","id":"jF8788AjyYTDSGnr0rgzJ1ivOGtuQxU9kz47w6Gbeng=_18f74256521:1030ee0:408b12aa","originId":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155875/tiktok-ai-generated-search-results-highlights-chatgpt","origin":{"streamId":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","htmlUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/"},"content":{"content":"<figure>\n<img alt=\"TikTok logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eqjKW9RxizgORJxA_QaB7dXXf6s=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345243/STK051_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_3_tiktok.0.jpg\">\n<figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>TikTok is testing a more robust search results page, including using generative AI. The feature appears to be a new and is called “search highlights.”</p>\n<p>A snippet of AI results appear at the top of some search results pages, and clicking into the section opens a new page with the full response. In quick tests, I was able to find AI results for queries about recipes or topics like “best laptops 2024.”</p>\n<div> <figure>\n<cite>Screenshot: TikTok</cite>\n<figcaption>Clicking the result takes you to a full screen page.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p>A page explaining the results says that the material is generated using ChatGPT, and that TikTok displays the content “when [the algorithm] finds them relevant to your search.” The feature appears to be limited so far: not all queries have AI...</p>\n<p>\n<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155875/tiktok-ai-generated-search-results-highlights-chatgpt\">Continue reading…</a>\n</p>","direction":"ltr"},"title":"TikTok is testing AI-generated search results","updated":1715640309000,"crawled":1715640558881,"published":1715640309000,"author":"Mia Sato","alternate":[{"type":"text/html","href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155875/tiktok-ai-generated-search-results-highlights-chatgpt"}],"visual":{"processor":"feedly-nikon-v3.1","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eqjKW9RxizgORJxA_QaB7dXXf6s=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345243/STK051_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_3_tiktok.0.jpg","width":1310,"height":873},"canonicalUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155875/tiktok-ai-generated-search-results-highlights-chatgpt","unread":true,"engagement":12,"engagementRate":0.33,"webfeeds":{"wordmark":"http://storage.googleapis.com/test-site-assets/PSNTZO8gXFUe-cpCZyApw0vEKWPT4b14D6teBEocIAE_owordmark-1503a52ff7f"}},{"language":"en","fingerprint":"6d580a93","originId":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155861/evolv-scanners-ai-gun-detection-nyc-subway-disney-eric-adams","id":"jF8788AjyYTDSGnr0rgzJ1ivOGtuQxU9kz47w6Gbeng=_18f73f63373:fd928c:58015665","origin":{"streamId":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","htmlUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/"},"title":"AI gun detection company name-dropped Disney in its successful pitch to NYC","updated":1715637149000,"crawled":1715637465971,"published":1715637149000,"content":{"direction":"ltr","content":"<figure>\n<img alt=\"Photo illustration of an NYPD officer in a subway station behind a pixelated gun.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kJPsYmncsiyku3MRzPF3HjaCvkY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345154/247066_Gun_Detectors_Subway_CVirginia_D.0.jpg\">\n<figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>When New York City Mayor Eric Adams was first introduced to a representative from Evolv, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/28/24114956/nyc-subway-ai-gun-detectors-evolv-technologies\">the AI gun detection company</a>, he was given a list of places the scanners could be used, including hospitals, schools, Times Square, and the Port Authority Bus Terminal. What seems to have persuaded Adams, according to <a href=\"https://www.wired.com/story/evolv-gun-detection-nyc-subways-emails/\">emails obtained by <em>Wired</em></a>, was Evolv’s disclosure of another major client: Disney.</p>\n<p>“As I mentioned, Linda Reid, VP Security for Walt Disney World (Florida) has known us since 2014 and deployed many of our systems at the Parks and Disney Springs,” Evolv co-founder Anil Chitkara wrote in an email to Adams’ office on February 7th, 2022. “They’ve had success screening for weapons with Evolv Express … There may be some interesting parallels...</p>\n<p>\n<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155861/evolv-scanners-ai-gun-detection-nyc-subway-disney-eric-adams\">Continue reading…</a>\n</p>"},"author":"Gaby Del Valle","alternate":[{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155861/evolv-scanners-ai-gun-detection-nyc-subway-disney-eric-adams","type":"text/html"}],"visual":{"processor":"feedly-nikon-v3.1","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kJPsYmncsiyku3MRzPF3HjaCvkY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345154/247066_Gun_Detectors_Subway_CVirginia_D.0.jpg","width":1310,"height":873},"canonicalUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155861/evolv-scanners-ai-gun-detection-nyc-subway-disney-eric-adams","unread":true,"engagement":10,"engagementRate":0.26,"webfeeds":{"wordmark":"http://storage.googleapis.com/test-site-assets/PSNTZO8gXFUe-cpCZyApw0vEKWPT4b14D6teBEocIAE_owordmark-1503a52ff7f"}},{"language":"en","fingerprint":"fcf08462","originId":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155816/google-9-pro-xl-lineup-leaked-images-design","id":"jF8788AjyYTDSGnr0rgzJ1ivOGtuQxU9kz47w6Gbeng=_18f73d4b45c:fb2a33:58015665","origin":{"streamId":"feed/http://theverge.com/rss/index.xml","title":"The Verge","htmlUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/"},"title":"Google’s Pixel 9 lineup appears in hands-on photos five months early","updated":1715635201000,"crawled":1715635270748,"published":1715635201000,"content":{"direction":"ltr","content":"<figure>\n<img alt=\"A photo of the Pixel 9, 9 Pro, and 9 Pro XL side by side.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QBaE3FqS8ppQ3ITlU2sth4t1chY=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345092/pixel9fam.0.jpeg\">\n<figcaption>Image: Rozetked</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>It’s a day that ends in Y, so naturally, we’re dealing with yet another Google Pixel hardware leak. This time, the Pixel 9, 9 Pro, and 9 Pro XL can be seen side by side in <a href=\"https://rozetked.me/news/33304-eksklyuziv-fotografii-vseh-modeley-google-pixel-9-ot-rozetked\">new images from <em>Rozetked</em></a> — a full five months before Google’s typical October release timeframe.</p>\n<p>I have many questions about how and why these units are out in the world so early, but here we are. And I know a lot of you are no doubt eyeing that regular 9 Pro, which will finally put Google’s very best camera chops into a normal-sized phone. Meanwhile, the 9 Pro XL looks a fair bit taller than Apple’s iPhone 15 Pro Max. </p>\n<figure>\n<cite>Image: <em>Rozetked</em></cite>\n<figcaption><em>Yep, that’s an XL-sized phone.</em></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>l’m a bit curious as to whether Google will still call this a “camera bar”...</p>\n<p>\n<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155816/google-9-pro-xl-lineup-leaked-images-design\">Continue reading…</a>\n</p>"},"author":"Chris Welch","alternate":[{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155816/google-9-pro-xl-lineup-leaked-images-design","type":"text/html"}],"visual":{"processor":"feedly-nikon-v3.1","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QBaE3FqS8ppQ3ITlU2sth4t1chY=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73345092/pixel9fam.0.jpeg","width":1310,"height":873},"canonicalUrl":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155816/google-9-pro-xl-lineup-leaked-images-design","unread":true,"engagement":8,"engagementRate":0.21,"webfeeds":{"wordmark":"http://storage.googleapis.com/test-site-assets/PSNTZO8gXFUe-cpCZyApw0vEKWPT4b14D6teBEocIAE_owordmark-1503a52ff7f"}}]}